## Workspace

Your workspace is at `workspace/`.
Use it for scratch files, intermediate outputs, and notes.

**Work Log:** `workspace/log.md`

## Available Commands

```bash
work ls                 # List subtasks with their status
work show <id>          # Show details of a subtask
work tree               # Show subtask dependency tree
work ready              # Show subtasks ready to work on
work active             # Show subtasks currently being worked on
work complete <id>      # Mark a subtask as complete
work run <id>           # Start a Claude Code session for a subtask
work rm <id>            # Remove a subtask
```
